1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:01:32,280 --> 00:01:40,640
[You are My Fateful Love]
[EP20]

3
00:01:41,560 --> 00:01:43,319
So on this last night, I'd like to

4
00:01:43,640 --> 00:01:45,040
share a song I wrote here

5
00:01:45,040 --> 00:01:45,959
in this little town

6
00:01:46,159 --> 00:01:47,000
and dedicate it to all of you.

7
00:01:48,079 --> 00:01:49,319
This song doesn't just belong to me,

8
00:01:50,079 --> 00:01:50,959
it also belongs to Shen'ao

9
00:01:52,040 --> 00:01:53,359
and to everyone here

10
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:56,840
so many of you as well.

11
00:01:57,200 --> 00:02:02,159
[Great! Great! Great!]

12
00:02:03,760 --> 00:02:06,439
[Great! Great! Great!]

13
00:03:50,319 --> 00:03:51,080
Happy birthday!

14
00:03:51,879 --> 00:03:52,719
May you become

15
00:03:52,719 --> 00:03:54,120
the person you truly want to be.

16
00:04:35,600 --> 00:04:36,680
[This journey in Shen'ao]

17
00:04:36,680 --> 00:04:37,800
[is coming to an end.]

18
00:04:38,600 --> 00:04:40,680
[I'm really glad that during this journey,]

19
00:04:41,040 --> 00:04:41,600
[I was able to figure out]

20
00:04:41,600 --> 00:04:42,680
[the questions that had been bothering me.]

21
00:04:43,319 --> 00:04:44,800
[And I also witnessed many people]

22
00:04:44,800 --> 00:04:46,160
[find answers of their own.]

23
00:04:46,839 --> 00:04:47,720
[About dreams...]

24
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:48,879
[About family...]

25
00:04:49,360 --> 00:04:50,279
[About love...]

26
00:04:50,839 --> 00:04:51,839
[And about life...]

27
00:04:52,639 --> 00:04:53,920
[Just like Li Shican said]

28
00:04:54,800 --> 00:04:56,120
[the me who leaves here]

29
00:04:56,639 --> 00:04:57,839
[is no longer the same person who arrived.]

30
00:04:58,920 --> 00:04:59,800
[I believe]

31
00:05:00,680 --> 00:05:01,759
[the answers we found]

32
00:05:01,759 --> 00:05:02,879
[along the way]

33
00:05:03,439 --> 00:05:04,639
[will stay with us]

34
00:05:05,319 --> 00:05:06,800
[and lead us toward a brighter]

35
00:05:06,959 --> 00:05:08,160
[more brilliant tomorrow.]

36
00:05:09,120 --> 00:05:11,720
[And if there are still some things]

37
00:05:11,720 --> 00:05:13,040
[that we can't quite figure out...]

38
00:05:16,040 --> 00:05:17,079
I've never told anyone

39
00:05:17,079 --> 00:05:18,120
about this,

40
00:05:20,279 --> 00:05:22,000
maybe I just need some time

41
00:05:22,519 --> 00:05:23,639
to really think it through,

42
00:05:24,839 --> 00:05:25,639
how to say it

43
00:05:26,680 --> 00:05:27,800
and where to even begin.

44
00:05:36,160 --> 00:05:37,439
Then take your time

45
00:05:38,879 --> 00:05:40,160
tell me when you're ready.

46
00:05:45,079 --> 00:05:47,240
[No rush, take it slow.]

47
00:05:48,279 --> 00:05:51,240
[There's still a long road ahead tomorrow.]

48
00:06:12,279 --> 00:06:13,160
Coming!

49
00:06:13,399 --> 00:06:14,480
Next time, just leave the package

50
00:06:14,480 --> 00:06:15,959
on the rack downstairs.

51
00:06:18,879 --> 00:06:19,360
Mingying.

52
00:06:21,959 --> 00:06:23,519
Listen to me, Mingying.

53
00:06:27,439 --> 00:06:28,279
Are you okay?

54
00:06:29,279 --> 00:06:30,279
Don't just stick your arm in like that?
Stretching it in like this?

55
00:06:32,560 --> 00:06:33,560
I'm afraid once the door closes,
I won't even get a chance to speak

56
00:06:34,360 --> 00:06:35,199
at all.

57
00:06:35,399 --> 00:06:36,639
If you have something to say, just say it.

58
00:06:38,240 --> 00:06:38,879
A new store opened
and it has a really good reputation,

59
00:06:39,639 --> 00:06:40,959
I specially got some for you to try.

60
00:06:41,279 --> 00:06:41,959
First of all,

61
00:06:42,560 --> 00:06:43,639
showing up without notice

62
00:06:43,639 --> 00:06:44,959
is considered really rude.

63
00:06:46,399 --> 00:06:47,839
You blocked me on WeChat.

64
00:06:47,839 --> 00:06:48,519
Second,

65
00:06:49,240 --> 00:06:50,199
giving food to someone who's on a diet
is also

66
00:06:50,759 --> 00:06:52,279
really, not polite at all.

67
00:06:52,519 --> 00:06:54,240
It's sugar-free, calorie-free, no worries.

68
00:06:58,759 --> 00:06:59,439
Lastly,

69
00:06:59,879 --> 00:07:01,759
when someone wants to be alone,

70
00:07:03,720 --> 00:07:04,720
any action you take

71
00:07:04,720 --> 00:07:06,120
is considered rude.

72
00:07:06,839 --> 00:07:07,439
Mingying,

73
00:07:07,439 --> 00:07:08,959
So those three points you just mentioned

74
00:07:08,959 --> 00:07:10,160
didn't clearly mean

75
00:07:10,160 --> 00:07:11,800
that you dislike me, right?

76
00:07:17,800 --> 00:07:19,759
Mingying, what's wrong?

77
00:07:29,199 --> 00:07:30,040
Coming back this time,

78
00:07:30,519 --> 00:07:31,720
everything feels taller somehow.

79
00:07:34,720 --> 00:07:36,199
That's just because you've been walking too long.

80
00:07:40,480 --> 00:07:42,720
Then I'll head upstairs first.

81
00:07:46,160 --> 00:07:46,879
Wait for me a second.

82
00:07:56,279 --> 00:07:56,879
What?

83
00:07:58,759 --> 00:07:59,439
This is for you.

84
00:08:09,959 --> 00:08:11,160
Later you went back to the shop

85
00:08:11,160 --> 00:08:12,240
and actually made it.

86
00:08:13,800 --> 00:08:15,720
Master Li taught me step by step.

87
00:08:16,759 --> 00:08:18,079
Master Li is super strict.

88
00:08:18,519 --> 00:08:21,079
You must've been scolded a lot while doing it, right?

89
00:08:21,360 --> 00:08:22,120
Of course not.

90
00:08:23,959 --> 00:08:24,480
No way.

91
00:08:29,399 --> 00:08:30,120
You've gotta give yourself
a little keepsake.

92
00:08:32,039 --> 00:08:32,679
Then,

93
00:08:39,320 --> 00:08:40,639
since you gave yours to me,

94
00:08:41,639 --> 00:08:44,240
I'll give mine to you in return.

95
00:08:57,519 --> 00:08:58,679
I'll head back first.

96
00:09:10,759 --> 00:09:11,639
I'll walk you upstairs.

97
00:09:17,960 --> 00:09:18,679
Be careful.

98
00:09:36,600 --> 00:09:38,720
Then I'll head back first.

99
00:09:53,200 --> 00:09:54,120
Since you're back,

100
00:09:55,799 --> 00:09:58,200
will the story keep going?

101
00:10:06,639 --> 00:10:08,360
Do you want me to keep writing it?

102
00:10:09,200 --> 00:10:09,960
Of course I do.

103
00:10:14,720 --> 00:10:17,720
Then let's see how the male lead behaves

104
00:10:18,240 --> 00:10:19,840
and how the heroine feels later.

105
00:10:23,080 --> 00:10:24,320
I'm talking about in the story.

106
00:10:27,840 --> 00:10:28,840
Looks like the male lead

107
00:10:30,480 --> 00:10:31,440
needs to try harder.

108
00:10:32,759 --> 00:10:34,120
He has to make the heroine happier.

109
00:10:37,639 --> 00:10:39,039
I'm talking about the story too.

110
00:10:49,600 --> 00:10:50,519
I'll head back first.

111
00:10:57,960 --> 00:10:58,720
Get some rest early.

112
00:10:59,799 --> 00:11:01,440
Be careful on your way home.

113
00:11:03,799 --> 00:11:04,240
Then

114
00:11:05,480 --> 00:11:06,279
I'll go first.

115
00:11:48,679 --> 00:11:50,200
[This light doesn't just illuminate people,]

116
00:11:50,399 --> 00:11:51,240
[but also]

117
00:11:52,480 --> 00:11:53,399
[lights up love.]

118
00:11:53,679 --> 00:11:54,840
Try turning it on.

119
00:12:00,320 --> 00:12:01,480
Wow, impressive.

120
00:12:02,039 --> 00:12:03,159
You are amazing.

121
00:12:03,720 --> 00:12:06,200
This little task is nothing for me.

122
00:12:06,559 --> 00:12:07,159
Alright.

123
00:12:08,600 --> 00:12:09,039
Take it slow.

124
00:12:27,360 --> 00:12:28,960
[Why is my heart racing so fast.]

125
00:12:30,279 --> 00:12:31,600
[Luckily before I came,]

126
00:12:31,600 --> 00:12:33,080
[I took a shower and changed.]

127
00:12:33,320 --> 00:12:34,480
[There's still a faint]

128
00:12:34,480 --> 00:12:35,759
[scent of laundry detergent on me.]

129
00:12:56,120 --> 00:12:58,480
[Oh god, Shen Mingying, what are you thinking?]

130
00:12:58,919 --> 00:13:00,519
[You're Ruan Yu's close friend.]

131
00:13:00,600 --> 00:13:02,159
[He's Xu Huaisong's sworn brother]

132
00:13:02,159 --> 00:13:04,200
[and also Ruan Yu's ex-blind date.]

133
00:13:04,399 --> 00:13:05,759
[And you with him…]

134
00:13:36,960 --> 00:13:37,919
[I'm home.]

135
00:13:37,960 --> 00:13:39,039
[Do you have time tonight?]

136
00:13:56,279 --> 00:13:57,600
Not answering so late.

137
00:13:58,240 --> 00:13:58,879
Where else could she be?

138
00:14:10,679 --> 00:14:11,519
Hey, Zhang Chuan.

139
00:14:11,919 --> 00:14:12,679
Um,

140
00:14:12,679 --> 00:14:13,840
Is Mingying with you?

141
00:14:14,120 --> 00:14:14,960
Who's this?

142
00:14:17,039 --> 00:14:18,039
Who are you?

143
00:14:18,240 --> 00:14:19,559
I'm his girlfriend's best friend.

144
00:14:20,200 --> 00:14:21,480
I'm his girlfriend.

145
00:14:22,960 --> 00:14:23,759
Sorry,

146
00:14:23,879 --> 00:14:24,960
I don't remember you being my friend.

147
00:14:25,519 --> 00:14:26,000
You…
Who is this?

148
00:14:27,639 --> 00:14:28,200
Zhang Chuan,
The way you're acting

149
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:30,080
is way too blatant.

150
00:14:30,320 --> 00:14:31,200
Who is she?
You better explain it to me!

151
00:14:32,360 --> 00:14:33,679
Listen to me, it's all a misunderstanding.

152
00:14:34,399 --> 00:14:36,080
I broke up with her a long time ago.

153
00:14:36,159 --> 00:14:37,240
Even if you broke up, you can't just…

154
00:14:38,679 --> 00:14:39,440
Break up?

155
00:14:41,919 --> 00:14:42,799
With a jerk like you,

156
00:14:42,799 --> 00:14:43,919
she should have broken up long ago.

157
00:14:44,200 --> 00:14:45,720
If we didn't break up, you'd call me a cheater.

158
00:14:46,039 --> 00:14:47,399
Break up, and you call me a jerk.

159
00:14:47,519 --> 00:14:48,320
Just shut up.

160
00:14:51,399 --> 00:14:52,360
Really broken up?

161
00:14:54,159 --> 00:14:55,679
I give it to you at the

162
00:14:55,679 --> 00:14:56,240
electrician's market price.

163
00:15:00,200 --> 00:15:00,799
No need.

164
00:15:02,200 --> 00:15:03,559
Talking money ruins feelings.

165
00:15:03,799 --> 00:15:05,240
Talking money actually avoids hurt feelings.

166
00:15:05,759 --> 00:15:06,919
Using money as an equal exchange

167
00:15:06,919 --> 00:15:09,080
is the fairest and easiest way to trade.

168
00:15:12,200 --> 00:15:13,799
But still, not everything

169
00:15:13,799 --> 00:15:15,519
can be measured with money.

170
00:15:16,799 --> 00:15:18,360
I used to think that way too.

171
00:15:18,440 --> 00:15:19,519
But now I know.

172
00:15:19,840 --> 00:15:21,759
Everything has a price.

173
00:15:27,440 --> 00:15:29,080
Alright, then you tell me

174
00:15:29,080 --> 00:15:30,360
I'm just here

175
00:15:30,360 --> 00:15:31,440
wanting to stay with you a bit longer.

176
00:15:31,440 --> 00:15:32,159
Put a price on it.

177
00:15:36,679 --> 00:15:37,480
That's not right.

178
00:15:39,840 --> 00:15:40,919
What I mean is,

179
00:15:40,919 --> 00:15:43,360
don't always rush me away.

180
00:15:46,200 --> 00:15:46,759
Why

181
00:15:46,759 --> 00:15:47,919
do you want to stay with me a bit longer?

182
00:15:48,399 --> 00:15:49,480
We've only met four times

183
00:15:49,480 --> 00:15:50,639
Today is the fifth.

184
00:15:50,639 --> 00:15:52,039
Are we soulmates forever

185
00:15:52,039 --> 00:15:53,240
or just fleeting as the ocean dries up?

186
00:15:53,519 --> 00:15:55,279
The last time between us

187
00:15:55,279 --> 00:15:56,679
was mutual consent.

188
00:15:58,639 --> 00:15:59,600
Between us

189
00:15:59,799 --> 00:16:01,080
neither side

190
00:16:01,080 --> 00:16:02,559
has to be responsible for the other.

191
00:16:03,440 --> 00:16:04,879
Now your one-sided feelings

192
00:16:04,879 --> 00:16:05,519
are bothering me.
So,

193
00:16:07,039 --> 00:16:07,879
take care, I won't see you out.

194
00:16:21,919 --> 00:16:22,679
I'm heading out now.
I've already sent you the money.

195
00:16:48,679 --> 00:16:49,919
[You broke up with Zhang Chuan?]

196
00:16:50,200 --> 00:16:51,200
[When did that happen?]

197
00:16:51,559 --> 00:16:52,279
[Are you home?]
[I'll come over right now.]

198
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:00,720
I just nodded off a moment ago.

199
00:17:01,720 --> 00:17:03,639
I'm fine, it's too late anyway.

200
00:17:03,639 --> 00:17:04,960
You don't have to come over.

201
00:17:07,759 --> 00:17:08,799
I'm already in the elevator.

202
00:17:11,240 --> 00:17:12,000
They won't run into each other, right?

203
00:17:15,519 --> 00:17:16,279
Ruan Yu, Ruan Yu.

204
00:17:16,680 --> 00:17:17,400
Ruan Yu, Ruan Yu.

205
00:17:18,960 --> 00:17:19,799
Shen Mingying.

206
00:17:19,799 --> 00:17:20,960
Ruan Yu.

207
00:17:20,960 --> 00:17:22,039
Do you even see me as...

208
00:17:22,039 --> 00:17:23,359
your best friend?

209
00:17:23,440 --> 00:17:24,160
Something this big, and...
you didn’t even tell me?

210
00:17:25,200 --> 00:17:25,839
It's because I

211
00:17:25,839 --> 00:17:27,240
see you as my best friend,

212
00:17:27,240 --> 00:17:28,759
I didn't want this silly stuff

213
00:17:28,759 --> 00:17:30,640
to ruin your mood.

214
00:17:32,559 --> 00:17:33,119
Good for you for breaking up.
A guy like that…

215
00:17:34,160 --> 00:17:35,359
You should've dumped him ages ago.

216
00:17:35,519 --> 00:17:35,960
Exactly.

217
00:17:36,759 --> 00:17:37,359
Listen,
I brought something from Shen'ao

218
00:17:37,839 --> 00:17:38,680
as a little gift for you.

219
00:17:39,279 --> 00:17:40,359
Close the door and let's talk inside.

220
00:17:48,799 --> 00:17:49,599
Let me tell you,

221
00:17:49,920 --> 00:17:50,799
this pomelo leaf water,
Is really, really good.

222
00:17:51,880 --> 00:17:52,839
When I went to Shen'ao,
the locals gave it to me.

223
00:17:53,799 --> 00:17:54,599
They said it can ward off bad luck.
I brought it here especially today.

224
00:17:55,480 --> 00:17:56,039
Right there.

225
00:17:57,119 --> 00:17:57,880
He usually sits there.
Bad vibes are strong there.

226
00:17:59,559 --> 00:18:00,240
Spray more.

227
00:18:03,799 --> 00:18:04,440
Spray here too.

228
00:18:05,119 --> 00:18:05,880
Yeah, right here.
Forget the flowers.

229
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:07,680
Spray the windows too.

230
00:18:13,720 --> 00:18:14,519
Did you just see that?

231
00:18:15,039 --> 00:18:15,799
A figure—someone.

232
00:18:16,079 --> 00:18:16,880
It just flashed by.

233
00:18:18,799 --> 00:18:19,519
You didn't see it?
No, I didn't.

234
00:18:20,960 --> 00:18:21,960
It's just the two of us here.

235
00:18:21,960 --> 00:18:23,000
Don't scare me.

236
00:18:23,279 --> 00:18:23,920
It's nothing, nothing.

237
00:18:24,279 --> 00:18:25,119
Maybe you're just tired these past couple days.
Your eyes might be a bit blurry.

238
00:18:26,000 --> 00:18:26,920
Yeah, that must be it.

239
00:18:26,920 --> 00:18:28,039
Go home and rest early.

240
00:18:29,079 --> 00:18:29,720
Nope.

241
00:18:30,319 --> 00:18:31,599
I haven't sprayed the bedroom yet.

242
00:18:32,079 --> 00:18:32,359
Hurry up.
Your room is really important.

243
00:18:33,200 --> 00:18:34,359
The room? Do we really need to?

244
00:18:34,359 --> 00:18:35,119
Come on, let's go now.

245
00:18:35,720 --> 00:18:36,960
There are plenty of good guys out there.

246
00:18:37,279 --> 00:18:38,319
At least 1.85 meters tall.

247
00:18:38,319 --> 00:18:40,519
Has abs, younger, playful and loyal type.

248
00:18:40,720 --> 00:18:41,599
The type you like.

249
00:18:41,599 --> 00:18:42,759
I'll keep an eye out for all of them for you.

250
00:18:43,400 --> 00:18:44,240
[1.85 meters.]

251
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:47,960
[That's about right.]

252
00:18:49,000 --> 00:18:49,759
But now,

253
00:18:49,759 --> 00:18:50,799
my taste has changed.

254
00:18:51,119 --> 00:18:53,599
I think 1.85 meters plus…

255
00:18:53,599 --> 00:18:54,880
it feels safe, sure,

256
00:18:54,880 --> 00:18:57,160
but when we argue, it's a bit overwhelming.

257
00:18:58,599 --> 00:18:59,839
[Abs…]

258
00:19:03,480 --> 00:19:05,440
[I'm starting to get the idea.]

259
00:19:05,720 --> 00:19:08,839
About abs… I

260
00:19:09,480 --> 00:19:11,279
don't have them myself, so

261
00:19:11,279 --> 00:19:12,000
I can't double standard.

262
00:19:13,480 --> 00:19:14,240
[Younger…]

263
00:19:15,480 --> 00:19:16,480
[Playful, loyal type.]

264
00:19:17,279 --> 00:19:19,759
But younger and playful types…

265
00:19:20,559 --> 00:19:21,960
Older ones take care of me.

266
00:19:22,559 --> 00:19:23,359
And the playful type…

267
00:19:23,359 --> 00:19:24,880
Isn't it different from a gentle Golden Retriever type, right?

268
00:19:25,200 --> 00:19:26,279
[How did it go from a wolf dog,]

269
00:19:26,279 --> 00:19:27,319
[to a Golden Retriever?]

270
00:19:28,519 --> 00:19:29,880
[What's a Golden Retriever type even like?]

271
00:19:40,039 --> 00:19:40,559
No, what you said
is so detailed and specific.

272
00:19:41,839 --> 00:19:42,640
Do you have a new target?

273
00:19:43,160 --> 00:19:43,599
Nope.

274
00:19:45,359 --> 00:19:46,359
This is still my fault.

275
00:19:46,799 --> 00:19:47,839
Lately,

276
00:19:47,839 --> 00:19:49,160
I've been too busy with my own stuff.

277
00:19:49,519 --> 00:19:51,000
Didn't even notice you broke up.

278
00:19:51,480 --> 00:19:52,160
How about this,

279
00:19:52,440 --> 00:19:53,400
